The paper deals with a filtering method based on deep learning for removing speckle noise from optical fringe patterns. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and regularization technology. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves image processing and signal processing techniques, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia). Additionally, the use of deep learning and regularization techniques suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
